cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about fine-grained visual categorization using a neural network architecture that incorporates attention and binary decision trees. The primary focus is on computer vision (CV) and machine learning (LG) techniques for image classification, which suggests that cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The use of attention and hierarchical feature learning also suggests that cs.AI and cs.MM are possible sub-categories. Finally, the use of back-propagation and optimization techniques suggests that cs.NE is a possible sub-category as well.
